Class HTMLFragmentComponent

  • All Implemented Interfaces:

    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractPageBodyMiddleComponent, AbstractSubHeader, EmptySubHeader, HolderIdComponent, OutComponent, PageBodyFooterComponent, PageBodyHeaderComponent, PageHeadScriptsComponent, PageLinksComponent, PageMetaTagsComponent, PageTitleComponent, PortalAdministrationFooterComponent, PortalAdministrationHeaderComponent, PortalSettingsNavigationComponent, PublisherFancyBoxScriptInjectorComponent, PublisherLumItemIdInjectorComponent, RenderPortalSettingsWorkPaneHeaderComponent, RenderWorkPaneHeaderComponent

    public abstract class HTMLFragmentComponent
extends org.apache.wicket.markup.html.WebComponent
    An abstract component to be used as a base for rendering a HTML fragment.

    The method getHTMLFragment(MarkupStream, ComponentTag) must be implemented returning the HTML fragment to be used.

    This class has better performance than a Label, because it doesn't have models and converters overhead. And if getHTMLFragment(MarkupStream, ComponentTag) returns a AppendingStringBuffer, it will prevent the call to Object.toString(), and the allocation of another string of the length of the HTML fragment.

    Since:
    6.0.0

      • getHTMLFragment

        protected abstract CharSequence getHTMLFragment(org.apache.wicket.markup.MarkupStream markupStream,
                                                org.apache.wicket.markup.ComponentTag openTag)
        Returns the HTML code fragment to be output by this component. Called during onComponentTagBody(MarkupStream, ComponentTag).

        A return type of AppendingStringBuffer prevents the allocation of another HTML fragment string instance.

        Parameters:
        markupStream - the markup stream.
        openTag - the open tag for the body.
        Returns:
        the HTML code fragment. A null return value will leave the body empty.
        Since:
        6.0.0
